  29.3.11 ESMF_LocalArrayIsCreated - Check whether a LocalArray object has been
  created

   INTERFACE:
   function ESMF_LocalArrayIsCreated(localarray, rc)

   RETURN VALUE:
     logical :: ESMF_LocalArrayIsCreated

   ARGUMENTS:
     type(ESMF_LocalArray), intent(in) :: localarray
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
     integer, intent(out), optional :: rc

   DESCRIPTION:

   Return .true. if the localarray has been created. Otherwise return
   .false.. If an error occurs, i.e. rc /= ESMF_SUCCESS is returned, the
   return value of the function will also be .false..

   The arguments are:

   localarray
          ESMF_LocalArray queried.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

